subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] noodles anyone?
author: Frank Sumption
full_text:
I see those eyes everywhere, but my interpretation different. I think it's
the eye sockets of skulls, a universal symbol of death and doom. Sometimes
the whole skull will show in these images. Charli Claypool used to call
these eyes Cat Eyes, she thought they looked like cats.

 When I see just the circles in the clouds, that means tornado's somewhere
east of here. Unpaired circles, the bigger the circle the bigger the storm.
there was one over the mountains for Katrina, it was huge where the entire
circumferencee of the circle was circulating on itself.

 Instead of noodles, how 'bout some nice vegible stew?


 F-S
